 a 18 wis hit to add 20 FR?<P>The arms I will get the HBB need more MR I think aye? :/<P>Earring of Essence great idea Droga is kinda a nice place  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif"><BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Rizena Halcyon</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"><BR>I'm by no means any kind of dragon raiding expert, but it's my understanding that you want your MR to be high is to resist the dragon roar(fear) spell. I'm not sure what MR is good enough.  As for wisdom, if you can get your FR up, you won't need to heal yourself.  Prevention is the best cure here IMO.  <P>Also, some other things I've thought of.. Bloodstained mantle = +10 MR<BR>Hand Woven Leggings = +10 FR<P>The amount of mana that you need is dependant on your tanks resists. When we went and did Faydedar, I threw 1 celestial heal on the Ranger and chain casted remedy on the Rogue. Ranger lived, Rogue Died.  Why? Resists.<P><BR>Riz<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Talura cwn'Zeylon</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Most dragon leaders say screw wisdom, the resists are more useful. Unless your wisdom is all in a few pieces you should be ok.<BR>Most likely the agro will shift around randomly, and I've almost found group heals to be more useful than trying to cel-heal or super-heal...which means you have to be in there with them. In my experience, it's more about being able to put enough people on him to get him to 40% then sending in the mages to lure.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Bodin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well...<P>I will dump wis till I am at 80 MR, 105raw FR should catch the Area fire spell  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif"> <P>Looks like i need to pick up cheal gear for feet, belt, shoulders, or a bracer to get 20 more MR  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/biggrin.gif"> Sitting at 159 wis now with 60 MR and 105 FR if I get the labeled gear on the profile.<P>From what I saw in /gui we had Nagie down to 10% when the last man fell. We where low resists ect, we knew it np. But...the figting took maybe 30 secs, all I plan to do when I go is dump may mana bar on group heals and Supheals for tanks that agro.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dikmer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Heh, I never did any of that, nor do I have a FR or a MR "suit". I always wore my normal gear. And out of maybe 18-22 naggy raids I went on, only once did we lose. And we regrouped and got him the second time.<P>As long as your TANKS have good resists and AC, you'll find having the wis/ac will be better.<P>Tanks are supposed to pull naggy to the door, then go past him into the lair so he turns around and hangs his tail out the door. If they can do this, you can stand on the last landing before the door and heal them just fine. No need to resist the Fear or the Fire.  You wont be in the area of effect.<P>The more wis/mana you have, the longer you can keep the tanks alive. If you get summoned, then your AC will protect you as you run back out from under him.<P>And by 51, you can stand around the corner and be even safer, because remedy has RANGE.<P>Only 2 things can cause a naggy raid to fail. Too many clerics getting killed (in which case, the tanks didn't have enough resists and forced the clerics to over heal, drawing aggro), or the clerics going OOM (In which case, either there weren't enough nukers to finish him off, or the tanks didn't have enough resists, forcing the clerics to manadump trying to keep them alive). <P>If your tanks have good gear, and you have enough nukers to finish him off, your FR/MR doesn't matter one bit.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
